<HEADLINE>
Taiwan stocks end sharply lower -- Sept. 15
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, Sept. 15 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Taiwan's share prices tumbled Monday, with the weighted index,
the market's key barometer, falling 258.23 points, or 4.09
percent, to close at 6,052.45, according to news reaching here
from Taipei.
</P>
<P>
Amid concern over the impact of the U.S. investment bank
LehmanBrothers' financial woes, the local bourse opened at
6,198.3 and fluctuated between 6,202.14 and 6,020.7. A total of
3.14 billion shares changed hands on market turnover of 72.94
billion new Taiwan dollars (2.27 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
All eight major stock categories lost ground, with construction
issues moving down the most at 6.8 percent. Cement stocks and
textile shares both declined 6.1 percent, banking and financial
issues shed 6 percent, paper and pulp issues lost 5.6 percent,
foodstuff stocks fell 5.1 percent, machinery and electronics
shares dropped 4 percent, and plastics and chemicals shares were
down 3.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 1,832 to 151, with 267 stocks
remaining unchanged.
</P>
